<p><strong>Questions and Answers</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What is the name of the statistics textbook written by Freedman, Pisani, and Purves?</strong>
Answer: Statistics, 4th Edition</p>
<p><strong>2. What are the main topics covered in the textbook?</strong>
Answer: Data analysis, descriptive statistics, statistical inference, probability, and linear regression</p>
<p><strong>3. Is the textbook available for free download as a PDF?</strong>
Answer: Yes, the textbook is available for free download as a PDF from various online sources such as Open Textbook Library and Google Books.</p>
<p><strong>4. What are the key features of the textbook?</strong>
Answer: The textbook features a conversational writing style, clear explanations, real-world examples, interactive simulations, and a wealth of exercises and problems.</p>
<p><strong>5. Is the PDF version of the textbook suitable for students and professionals?</strong>
Answer: Yes, the PDF version of the textbook is suitable for both students studying statistics and professionals looking to refresh or expand their knowledge in the field. However, it's important to note that the PDF version may not include all the interactive simulations and exercises found in the print version.</p>